translated: Hahn, John-Alfred Emanuel, district veterinarian, Kvänum, born on the 26th of a month in Stockholm to Captain Alfr. Em. H. and Ester Kullenberg. Married in 1932 to Ingrid Johansson. They have three children: Inger Gunilla born in 1935, Monica born in 1939, and Lena Margareta born in 1941. John-Alfred graduated from veterinary school in 1925, became a licensed veterinarian in 1930, and practiced in Tungelsta, Skärplinge, Edsbyn, Fjärdhundra, Brålanda, Storvik, N. Råda, Hammenhög, Kungsbacka, Ystad, Töreboda, Simrishamn, and Skog from 1927 until 1931. He then became a district veterinarian in Pajala in 1932, in Hova in 1937, and in Kvänum in 1947. He also worked as an inspector for the meat inspection agency in Hova from 1940 to 1946, and in the contracting butchery from 1942 to 1946. He served as chairman of the tax commission in Pajala in 1934, and on the health commission from 1933 to 1937.
